description: Provides details of a notebook execution.

parameters.name: NotebookExecutionId
parameters.description: The unique identifier of the notebook execution.

nested_items.name: NotebookExecution
nested_items.description: Properties of the notebook execution.

nested_items.name: NotebookExecutionId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of a notebook execution.

nested_items.name: EditorId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the Amazon EMR Notebook that is used for the notebook execution.

nested_items.name: ExecutionEngine
nested_items.description: The execution engine, such as an Amazon EMR cluster, used to run the Amazon EMR notebook and perform the notebook execution.

nested_items.name: Id
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the execution engine. For an Amazon EMR cluster, this is the cluster ID.

nested_items.name: Type
nested_items.description: The type of execution engine. A value of EMR specifies an Amazon EMR cluster.

nested_items.name: MasterInstanceSecurityGroupId
nested_items.description: An optional unique ID of an Amazon EC2 security group to associate with the master instance of the Amazon EMR cluster for this notebook execution. For more information see Specifying Amazon EC2 Security Groups for Amazon EMR Notebooks in the EMR Management Guide.

nested_items.name: ExecutionRoleArn
nested_items.description: The execution role ARN required for the notebook execution.

nested_items.name: NotebookExecutionName
nested_items.description: A name for the notebook execution.

nested_items.name: NotebookParams
nested_items.description: Input parameters in JSON format passed to the Amazon EMR Notebook at runtime for execution.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: The status of the notebook execution.
START_PENDING indicates that the cluster has received the execution request but execution has not begun.
STARTING indicates that the execution is starting on the cluster.
RUNNING indicates that the execution is being processed by the cluster.
FINISHING indicates that execution processing is in the final stages.
FINISHED indicates that the execution has completed without error.
FAILING indicates that the execution is failing and will not finish successfully.
FAILED indicates that the execution failed.
STOP_PENDING indicates that the cluster has received a StopNotebookExecution request and the stop is pending.
STOPPING indicates that the cluster is in the process of stopping the execution as a result of a StopNotebookExecution request.
STOPPED indicates that the execution stopped because of a StopNotebookExecution request.

nested_items.name: StartTime
nested_items.description: The timestamp when notebook execution started.

nested_items.name: EndTime
nested_items.description: The timestamp when notebook execution ended.

nested_items.name: Arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the notebook execution.

nested_items.name: OutputNotebookURI
nested_items.description: The location of the notebook execution's output file in Amazon S3.

nested_items.name: LastStateChangeReason
nested_items.description: The reason for the latest status change of the notebook execution.

nested_items.name: NotebookInstanceSecurityGroupId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the Amazon EC2 security group associated with the Amazon EMR Notebook instance. For more information see Specifying Amazon EC2 Security Groups for Amazon EMR Notebooks in the Amazon EMR Management Guide.

nested_items.name: Tags
nested_items.description: A list of tags associated with a notebook execution. Tags are user-defined key-value pairs that consist of a required key string with a maximum of 128 characters and an optional value string with a maximum of 256 characters.

nested_items.name: Key
nested_items.description: A user-defined key, which is the minimum required information for a valid tag. For more information, see Tag.

nested_items.name: Value
nested_items.description: A user-defined value, which is optional in a tag. For more information, see Tag Clusters.

nested_items.name: NotebookS3Location
nested_items.description: The Amazon S3 location that stores the notebook execution input.

nested_items.name: Bucket
nested_items.description: The Amazon S3 bucket that stores the notebook execution input.

nested_items.name: Key
nested_items.description: The key to the Amazon S3 location that stores the notebook execution input.

nested_items.name: OutputNotebookS3Location
nested_items.description: The Amazon S3 location for the notebook execution output.

nested_items.name: Bucket
nested_items.description: The Amazon S3 bucket that stores the notebook execution output.

nested_items.name: Key
nested_items.description: The key to the Amazon S3 location that stores the notebook execution output.

nested_items.name: OutputNotebookFormat
nested_items.description: The output format for the notebook execution.

nested_items.name: EnvironmentVariables
nested_items.description: The environment variables associated with the notebook execution.
